Sentencas: In this study, perovskite-type oxides of Sr2Fe1+xMo1-xO6-delta, (x = 0, 0.2, 0.35, 0.5) were synthesized and the phase stabilities both in oxidizing and reducing atmosphere were investigated.
Titulo: Sr2Fe1+xMo1-xO6-δ as anode material of cathode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: When calcined in the air atmosphere, pure perovskite phase can be obtained for the composition of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta while a large portion of SrMoO4 second phase was detected in other compositions.
Titulo: Sr2Fe1+xMo1-xO6-δ as anode material of cathode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Further reducing the above powders showed a pure phase for Sr2Fe1+xMo1-xO6-delta (x = 0, 0.2, 0.35) while minor amount of Fe was precipitated from the Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta.
Titulo: Sr2Fe1+xMo1-xO6-δ as anode material of cathode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Due to the highest electrical conductivity and lowest polarization resistance of Sr2FeMoO6-delta, such composition has been applied as the cell anode for a cathode supported solid oxide fuel cell (CS-SOFC).
Titulo: Sr2Fe1+xMo1-xO6-δ as anode material of cathode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Maximum power densities of 463 and 331 mW cm(-2) have obtained for the fuel cell when measured at 800 degrees C using hydrogen and propane as fuel, respectively.
Titulo: Sr2Fe1+xMo1-xO6-δ as anode material of cathode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The durability test in propane indicated that Sr2FeMoO6-delta could be a potential anode material with good tolerance ability toward coking formation.
Titulo: Sr2Fe1+xMo1-xO6-δ as anode material of cathode-supported solid oxide fuel cells
